<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="752" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Department
                                        of State</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-31"><hi rend="italic">August 31,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have received your dispatch, No. 287. This Government thinks it has a
                            right to expect full compliance with promise to issue iradé to Marsovan
                            College. Delay incomprehensible.</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>